<p class="kicker">Strategy</p>
<h1>Persona Development – Target Audience Characterisation Close to the Real Customer</h1>
<p>A developed persona represents the purchasing habits of your target group. We develop such a virtual example person with the analysed data collections and add possible behavioural scenarios. This allows you to identify improvement potential for your online shop and strategically place new marketing campaigns with wide reach and low scatter in your market segment using the What if principle.</p>
</div></section>
<div class="content">
<h2>Persona Development for Digital Strategies by Hob by Horse</h2>
<p>For persona development, the data from your target audience analysis is summarised into character bundles. From the values with the highest and lowest key figures, a theoretical customer character emerges with habits, scepticism, emotional expectations and targeted purchasing behaviour. Such a virtual ideal customer is then helpful for building strategically sensible content marketing, SEO components or paid media.</p>
<h2>Most Important Stages of Persona Development</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Define objectives:</strong> Do you want more clicks on your display ads or stronger appeal to your landing page? Depending on the strategic goal, the selected persona has demographic characteristics such as everyday life, lifestyle and life aspirations. With a fictitious name, a tailored life quote and an assigned image, this becomes a virtual person who could possibly act one way or another.</li>
<li><strong>Data collection for the persona:</strong> The more sources you use for data collection, the more concrete the characterisation becomes. Valuable analysis sources include Google Analytics, Google Ads, social media followers and newsletter subscribers.</li>
<li><strong>Summarise data in a structured way:</strong> Now we form customer groups from the collected data, such as stressed young professionals or long-established nature lovers of older age. The more data attributes that can be assigned per group, the more closely aligned with the customer future marketing campaigns can be.</li>
<li><strong>Create a sedcard for the persona:</strong> Fill in the sedcard according to a Top Ten principle (demographic data, name, image, personally typical information, behaviour when searching for and in online shops). We find out, tailored to your business model, which websites the persona prefers, how actively they operate on social media channels and how strongly they are interested in news and current affairs.</li>
</ul>
<p><em>"When you speak to everyone, you speak to no one." (© Meredith Hill)</em></p>
<h2>Industry Relevance of Persona Development</h2>
<p>In terms of industry focus, persona development is a real playground. Fashion-interested customers and trendsetters in the lifestyle sector change their search habits and personal interests particularly frequently. E-commerce customers in the automotive or packaging industry are more focused on bare facts and generally topic-faithful for long periods. The hospitality and gastronomy industry is also subject to constant change in search behaviour and interests.</p>
<h2>Target Group Benefits with Persona Concretisation by Hob by Horse</h2>
<p>Your B2B, B2C or D2C target groups will notice when your online shop can practically anticipate their every search wish from the input. The shopping experience improves through strategic navigation offers, active calls to action and inviting marketing campaigns. Where your target group feels at home once, they are happy to return again and again.</p>
